item.title: University of Central Florida
item.description: The University of Central Florida celebrated it's 50th anniversary celebration in 2013. Located in Orlando, Florida, UCF has grown to become the second-largest university in the U.S.A. Our 12 colleges offer over 200 different bachelors, masters, PhD and professional degrees. Students have come from all 50 states and 140 countries to live, learn and grow at this dynamic school. In 2013, UCF also became one of 40 public universities with The Carnegie Foundation's highest designation in two categories: community engagement and research activity.
